The Problem Looks Normal
Many Angular applications start with clean components.
But as requirements grow, developers keep adding logic to the component while services remain simple wrappers around HTTP calls.
Eventually, the component becomes the brain of the feature.
@Component({
selector: 'app-customer-page',
templateUrl: './customer-page.html'
})
export class CustomerPageComponent {private readonly customerApi = inject(CustomerApi);
customers = signal<Customer[]>([]);
loading = signal(false);
loadCustomers() {
this.loading.set(true);
this.customerApi.getCustomers().subscribe({
next: customers => {
const activeCustomers = customers.filter(
customer => customer.status === 'ACTIVE'
);
activeCustomers.sort((a, b) =>
a.name.localeCompare(b.name)
);
this.customers.set(activeCustomers);
this.loading.set(false);
}
});
}
}
The service simply returns HTTP data.
